<Layout title="About Us - Hoogly" description="Learn about Hoogly's mission, values, and leadership team." type="website">
  <section class="about-hero text-center" style="padding: 4rem 0 2rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-title" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0.2em; font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;">
        <div class="hero-title-align" style="display: block;">
          <span class="hero-title-text">The </span><span class="hero-highlight"><span class="hero-highlight-text">Hoogly Manifesto</span></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-subtitle" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; text-align: left; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; padding-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        We're not here to run surveys. We're here to rebuild trust.
      </div>
      <p class="anonymous-ai-subheadline" style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.8;">
        For too long, employee engagement has been reduced to metrics.<br/>
        A dashboard. A heatmap. A bar chart with decimals.<br/><br/>
        We've seen the Friday "pulse" surveys that nobody trusts.<br/>
        We've watched participation drop—and silence get misread as satisfaction.<br/>
        We've met HR leaders armed with data but no direction.<br/>
        And we've sat with managers who genuinely want to do better… but are handed a 27-page PDF and told, "Good luck."<br/><br/>
        Let's be honest: the way we've tried to measure culture is broken.<br/>
        Asking the same five questions over and over isn't listening.<br/>
        And getting answers you can't act on? That's not insight. That's noise.<br/><br/>
        Real engagement doesn't come from another survey.<br/>
        It comes from conversation. From curiosity.<br/>
        From creating space where people can share what's really going on—without fear or filters.<br/><br/>
        It starts with trust. Not state-of-the-art encryption (though we have that too).<br/>
        But trust in intent. Trust in what happens next.<br/>
        Trust that when someone speaks up, it won't just be logged—it will be heard.<br/><br/>
        That's why we built Hoogly.<br/>
        Not to collect more data.<br/>
        But to make sense of it.<br/>
        Not to give you more "shoulds."<br/>
        But to help you actually do the things that make a difference.<br/><br/>
        Our AI doesn't just ask. It listens.<br/>
        It distills the sentiment, protects anonymity, and translates feelings into direction.<br/>
        It helps managers know where to start.<br/>
        And it stays with them as they follow through—with coaching, nudges, and Culture Agents who care as much as they do.<br/><br/>
        We're not here to help companies look like they care.<br/>
        We're here to help them actually care—in ways their people can feel.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

